HEADWORD: Orsellinic
<hw>Or`sel*lin"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, an organic acid obtained by a
partial decomposition of orsellic acid as a white crystalline substance,
and related to protocatechuic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

